True Strike						KEY:Pseudonatural ~ True Strike			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Race Trait.Pseudonatural Race Trait.SpecialQuality								DESC:Once per day, a pseudonatural creature can gain a +20 insight bonus on a single attack roll. In addition, the creature suffers no miss chance against a target that has concealment or total concealment when making this attack.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															BONUS:VAR|TrueStrikePerDay|1																	SOURCEPAGE:p.161
Resistance						KEY:Pseudonatural ~ Resistance			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Race Trait.Pseudonatural Race Trait.SpecialQuality								DESC:A pseudonatural creature has resistance to acid and electricity based on the base creature's Hit Dice (see the table below).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Resistance to Acid|Resistance to Electricity																							BONUS:VAR|AcidResistanceBonus|5+((HD>=8)*5)	BONUS:VAR|ElectricityResistanceBonus|5+((HD>=8)*5)					SOURCEPAGE:p.161
Damage Reduction					KEY:Pseudonatural ~ Damage Reduction		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Race Trait.Pseudonatural Race Trait.SpecialQuality								DESC:A pseudonatural creature gains damage reduction based on the base creature's Hit Dice (see the table below).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.161
Spell Resistance					KEY:Pseudonatural ~ Spell Resistance		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Extraordinary.Race Trait.Pseudonatural Race Trait.SpecialQuality			DEFINE:PseudonaturalSR|0	DESC:A pseudonatural creature gains spell resistance equal to 10 + the base creature's HD (maximum 25).																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																				BONUS:VAR|PseudonaturalSR|min(25,10+HD)											SR:PseudonaturalSR	SOURCEPAGE:p.161
Alternate Form					KEY:Pseudonatural ~ Alternate Form			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Supernatural.Race Trait.Pseudonatural Race Trait.SpecialQuality								DESC:As a standard action, a pseudonatural creature can take the form of a grotesque, tentacled mass (or another appropriately gruesome form, as determined by the DM). Despite the alien appearance, its abilities remain unchanged. Other creatures receive a -1 morale penalty on their attack rolls against a pseudonatural creature when it is in this alternate form.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.161

